<HEADLINE> Ethiopian TV Producer Wishes to Cooperate with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- An Ethiopian television
producer has expressed his wishes to join hands with Chinese firms
in producing TV sets and other household electronic appliances.
</P>
<P>
Tebarek Hassen, general manager of the United Tebarek and
Family Private Limited Company, told Xinhua that he was looking
forward to have cooperation with Chinese counterparts in a bid to
expand Ethiopian TV industry.
</P>
<P>
"I am open to work with Chinese," Tebarek said, noting that any
form of cooperation, including assembling of TV spare parts from
China and China's investment in form of technique and machinery,
would be welcome.
</P>
<P>
The United Tebarek and Family Private Limited Company, which
became operational on May 8, 1999, is the first and only TV
producer ever established in the Horn of Africa country.
</P>
<P>
Tebarek, who personally invested 4.5 million birr (about
562,000 U.S. dollars) to build the TV assemble plant, has begun
exporting 21-inch color TV set.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of TV sets produced in the factory was
transported to Zimbabwe early this week. Zimbabwe is to import
1,000 21-inch color TV sets from Ethiopia during the next six
months, he said, adding that Tanzania and some other African
countries are also studying to import TV sets from Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian TV assemble plant currently imports spare parts
from Turkey.
</P>
<P>
According to Tebarek, the factory is to employ some 1,500
staff, and to increase its production capacity from 100 to 1,500
TV sets per day following the completion of its expansion program.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
