<HEADLINE> Angola to Distribute UN Relief Food </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 5 (xinhua) -- Angolan government will be
responsible for distributing food and medicine in humanitarian
aids to people in need around the war-torn country, while the
amount of displaced people in Angola reached two million.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Humanitarian Assistance Coordination Technical Unit
(UTCAH) announced in Luanda Thursday that due to the deteriorating
humanitarian situation, the organization will permit the Angolan
government to help distribute humanitarian materials.
</P>
<P>
The government will be responsible for deciding areas enjoying
priority in assistance and escorting food and other necessities of
life to the people in need, said a UTCAH source.
</P>
<P>
With an aim to help the residents in terrible distress, UCAH
decided to open a "humanitarian corridor" leading to Malanje
Province, facing the most serious humanitarian crisis and enjoying
priority in humanitarian aids together with Bie and Cuando Cubango
provinces.
</P>
<P>
General Director of UTCAH Palmira Tjipilica confirmed Wednesday
that in Angola, the amount of the displaced people had reached two
million by the end of July, with 700,000 of them, 35 percent of
the total, suffering hunger and lacking emergency assistance.
</P>
<P>
Tjipilica said the humanitarian situation in Angola is "very
very grave".
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
