<HEADLINE> Three People Killed in U.S. Shootings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Three people were shot to
death Thursday morning at two companies in Pelham of Alabama State
in the United States, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted local police sources as saying that a
34-year-old suspect was arrested after a brief scuffle when
officers approached his car.
</P>
<P>
Pelham Police Chief Allan Wade said the suspect worked at
Ferguson Enterprises, where two of the victims were shot inside
the company, and was a former employee of Post Airgas, where
another victim was shot to death a short time later.
</P>
<P>
The latest shootings came one week after a frustrated investor
killed nine people and injured 13 others at two brokerage firms in
Atlanta City, Georgia State, in one of the worst office massacres
ever in the United States. Pelham is 230 kilometers west of
Atlanta. 
</P>
</TEXT>
