great importance to developing cooperative ties with Libya and
will contribute to Libya's erasing of the land mines planted by
Italy during the colonization period.
</P>
<P>
The lifting of the sanctions, which were imposed on Libya
following the 1988 Pan Am bombing over Lockerbie, has allowed
Tripoli to take part in the dialogue among the Mideterranean basin
countries, he added, noting that Italy calls for helping Libya
play a "substantial role" in the dialogue.
</P>
<P>
This is Dini's second visit to the north African country this
year. He paid the first visit to Libya on April 5 shortly after
the lifting of the U.N.-imposed embargo on the country.
</P>
<P>
The Italian minister is scheduled to have a meeting with Libyan
leader Colonel Muammar Gaddafi at a later time.
</P>
<P>
Italy is a major trade partner of Libya.
</P>
<P>
Dini's visit took place a few days after the Italian Eni Group
for Oil and Gas signed a contract with the Libyan authorities on
the gas exploitation and the gas pipe line between Libya and
Sicily with a total investment of 5.5 billion U.S. dollars.
