<HEADLINE> Egyptian FM Receives Message from Thai Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr
Moussa on Thursday received a message from his Thai counterpart
Surin Pitsuwan.
</P>
<P>
The message was handed over to Egyptian Assistant Foreign
Minister for Asian Affairs Nagi al-Ghatrifi by Thailand's
ambassador in Cairo, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The message focused on the planned meetings of the
Egyptian-Thai Joint Committee due to be held in Cairo in October
under the chairmanship of the foreign ministers, the news agency
said.
</P>
<P>
During the meetings, the two countries will sign a number of
agreements.
</P>
<P>
The agreements include one on protecting reciprocal
investments, another on avoiding dual taxation, and a third on
political consultations between the two foreign ministries.
</P>
<P>
During the committee meetings, a council grouping Egyptian and
Thai businessmen will be formed in an effort to bolster trade and
economic cooperation and increase investments between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Egypt and Thailand maintain good relations. Officials of the
two countries have expressed keenness on further promoting
bilateral cooperations, in the economic and trade areas in
particular.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has been exerting efforts in recent years to attract
foreign investments and seek ways of increasing exports.
</P>
