<HEADLINE> Taliban Confirm Fall of Three Towns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The Taliban's senior official
responsible for information, Amir Khan Muttaqi, Thursday confirmed
the fall of Charikar, Jabel Saraj and Gulbahar to the opposition
forces, sources from Kabul told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Thursday, opposition spokesman Abdullah (eds: one
name) said the forces loyal to former defense minister Ahmad Shah
Masood recaptured the three towns in an overnight surprise counter
offensive.
</P>
<P>
The opposition troops moved out of the Panjsher valley late
Wednesday night and took Gulbahar at the entrance of the valley
and then pushed westwards to take Jabel Saraj, some 70 kilometers
north of Kabul, Abdullah said.
</P>
<P>
Then the troops moved southwards and captured Charikar, the
capital of Parwan province.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban militia last week launched a major offensive and
forced the Masood forces to retreat to the heavily fortified
Panjsher valley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
