<HEADLINE> Greece Reduces Gas Taxes to Curb Inflation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Fuel prices in Greece dropped by
three drachmas (about 300 drachmas equal one U.S. dollar) as of
Thursday, a result of the country's reduction of consumption taxes
in order to contain inflation.
</P>
<P>
The measure, in effect from Thursday until June 30 next year,
would cost Greece about 22.5 billion drachmas, but would benefit
the inflation rate by an annual 0.1 percent, the semi-official
Athens News Agency (ANA) reported. 
</P>
