<HEADLINE> Greece to Launch New Derivatives Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Greece would launch its new
derivatives market on August 27 this year.
</P>
<P>
Sixteen brokerages and four banks, including the National Bank
of Greece, were ready to sign the contracts with the Athens
Derivatives Market, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA)
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Until the end of the year, the banks would act as members of
the clearing house and take part in non-equities derivatives
trading, which is due to be introduced in the autumn. 
