<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Records Set At IPE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON August 5 (Xinhua) - The International Petroleum
Exchange's (IPE) Gas Oil figures reached new levels when the
contract traded 57,778 lots Wednesday compared to 56,332 lots
traded on 11 January 1996.
</P>
<P>
IPE said Thursday that Russia's decision to severely reduce
exports of gas oil, fuel oil and gasoline was the apparent reason
for the increase in activity.
</P>
<P>
Total traded volume for July 1999 reached 89,294 lots, a 23
percent increase on the previous record set in July 1998 when
volumes traded at 72,573 lots.
</P>
<P>
In response to demand the IPE plans to extend Gas Oil and
Natural Gas futures in October this year.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, Gas Oil futures will be extended from 18
months to three years and Natural Gas will be extended from 15
months to three years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
