<DOCNO> XIE19990806.0054 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Explosion at Romanian Steel Plant Kills Three People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 5 (Xinhua) -- A strong explosion on Thursday
killed three and injured ten workers at Romania's SIDEX Galati
steel combine.
</P>
<P>
According to the official Rompres news agency, the chimney of
the furnace 4 of the combine blew up on Thursday morning, killing
one woman and one man on the spot. Another man died en route to
the hospital. 14 employees hurt by the explosion were taken to the
county hospital.
</P>
<P>
According to SIDEX General Manager Ionel Bors, the blast seemed
to be a technical accident caused by accumulations of gas which
turned into an explosive mixture due to the high temperatures.
</P>
<P>
Prefect's office, police and fire brigade investigations are
under way at the accident site, and a special committee has been
set up to further investigate the accident.
</P>
<P>
Situated 240 km east of Bucharest, SIDEX Galati operates six
furnaces and is the most important steel producer in Romania,
producing one third of the country's total steel output of some
six million tonnes.
</P>
<P>
A similar explosion occurred at SIDEX in 1998, with furnace 6,
with two casualties reported. In 1994, a blast at one of SIDEX's
furnaces killed four workers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
