<HEADLINE> India expels Pakistan High Commission Staff Member </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 6 (Xinhua) --India Friday expelled a Pakistan
High Commission staffer on charges of spying and asked him to
leave the country within a week, PTI reported.
</P>
<P>
"Mohammad Safdar, a staff member of the Pakistan High
Commission, was indulging in activities incompatible with his
official status and Pakistan has been asked to withdraw him from
India by August 12, 1999," official sources said here.
</P>
<P>
In Islamabad, a Pakistani official statement denied the charge
and termed the expulsion as part of a continuing "harassment
campaign" against Pakistani staffers in India. 
