<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, August 6 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM -- Vehicle-maker Volvo AB announced Friday that it
has acquired the rival Swedish truck and bus maker Scania after
taking a majority share in the company.
</P>
<P>
Volvo President and Chief Executive Leif Johansson told a news
conference Friday that under an acquisition deal reached between
Volvo and Investor AB, the investment arm of Sweden's powerful
Wallenberg family, Volvo should take over a 49 percent stake in
Scania that had been owned by Investor AB.
</P>
<P>
Volvo also offered to buy the rest of Investor AB's share in
Scania in the deal valued at 60.7 billion kronor (7.4 billion U.S.
dollars). The deal gives Volvo 69.6 percent of the votes in
Scania.
</P>
<P>
Volvo began its push to acquire Scania in January, several
weeks before announcing the sale of its passenger car division to
Ford Motors.
</P>
<P>
After the acquisition, Scania will constitute a division within
Volvo, with its trademarks and distribution staying separate from
Volvo.
</P>
<P>
The acquisition, which must be approved by the European Union,
would create the world's second-largest manufacturer of trucks and
buses, behind DaimlerChrysler.(Sweden-Volvo-Merger)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Two destroyers of the South Korean Navy made a port
call to the western Japanese port of Sasebo on Friday after
concluding a joint naval exercise with Japan's Maritime Self-
Defense Force (MSDF) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
King Kwanggaeto, a 3,855-ton destroyer loaded with helicopters,
and Chung Nam, a 2,180-ton destroyer, became the first South
Korean navy warships to visit Japan.
</P>
<P>
South Korean Navy officers will visit the Sasebo city office
and meet with Japanese counterparts to brief them on the drill.
The two military vessels are scheduled to depart on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The two destroyers, together with three warships from Japan's
MSDF, participated in the search-and-rescue drills conducted in
the East China Sea Between Japan's westernmost main island of
Kyushu and the Cheju Island, south of the Korean Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
The drill, in which the five ships trained for responding to
fires on civilian vessels, marked the two countries' first joint
military exercise.
</P>
<P>
The drill drew strong criticism from the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK), which described the maneuver on Thursday
as a prelude to a new Japanese invasion. (Japan-South Korea-
Destroyers)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- More than 100,000 postcards have been received since
January 1998 when two young girls from the United States launched
their "One Million Postcrd Campaign" against the sanctions on Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"Our goal is to collect one million postcards to President
