<HEADLINE> Chinese Cultural Circles Criticize Lee Teng-hui's"Two States" Statement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- People from Chinese cultural
circles gathered at a forum here today to condemn Lee Teng-hui's "
two states" statement, which reveals his evil motives to split the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
The people on China's mainland and Taiwan share the same
history and cultural background, and are longing for the
reunification of the motherland, said the attendants at the forum,
who have been to Taiwan many times for cultural exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Lee will only achieve notoriety by trying to split the country,
going against the people's will, they agreed.
</P>
<P>
"I have been to Taiwan three times for exchanges and
cooperation with my counterparts there," said Yang Xin, deputy
curator of the Palace Museum here.
</P>
<P>
Yang said that his Taiwan counterparts often expressed their
hope that the relics transported by the Kuomintang (KMT, the
Taiwan authorities) from the Palace Museum in Beijing to Taipei
would be returned to Beijing one day, and that Taiwan would return
to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Leading cultural figures and famous artists also voiced their
disapproval of Lee's "two states" statement at today's forum, and
expressed their determination to safeguard China's sovereignty and
territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
Also today, the Ministry of Justice held a forum to condemn Lee
Teng-hui's "two states" statement. Officials from the ministry
showed their firm stand of opposing the "two states" statement and
other statements, including "independence for Taiwan", "two Chinas
" and "one China, one Taiwan", which are aimed at splitting the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
