<HEADLINE> Bearish Sentiments Prevail in Karachi Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, Pakistan, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Bearish sentiments
prevailed on the Karachi Stock Exchange Friday when the key
indicator fell for the fourth consecutive day.
</P>
<P>
The 100-share price index closed the week at 1,207.89 points,
26.35 points, or 2.13 percent, lower from Thursday's 1,234.24
points.
</P>
<P>
The volume traded Friday stood at 176.407 million shares
against Thursday's 270.452 million shares.
</P>
<P>
The postponement of talks between Hubco officials and the
government on the settlement of a power tariff dispute caused
market players to offload, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
Hubco, the largest private power producing company with a
weightage of 18 percent of the index, fell by 1 rupee to 19.70
rupees on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 176 active issues, losers beat gainers 88 to 47
while 41 remained unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
