<HEADLINE> Indian Government to Set Up Eco-Clubs for Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 6 (Xinhua) -- In a move to make students
aware of the environment and ecology, the Indian government has
proposed to set up 1,000 eco-clubs in middle and secondary schools
in 1999.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said Friday that the objective of the
clubs would be to motivate children to keep their surroundings
green and clean, to encourage them to say "No" to the use of
plastic bags and promote afforestation and tree plantation in
their surroundings.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, each school will be given a grant of 4,000
rupees (93 U.S. dollars) per year and at the end of each year, the
performance of the schools will be monitored by the Department of
Environment and the best will be given a trophy and a cash prize.
</P>
</TEXT>
