<HEADLINE> Commentary: Nature of "Special State-to-State Relations" Statement is Splittism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- An Xinhua News Agency commentary
today stresses that the real nature of Lee Teng-hui's "special
state-to-state relations" statement is splittism, not promoting
the level of cross-Straits talks, as the Taiwan authorities have
claimed.
</P>
<P>
It says the written speech of Koo Chenfu, chairman of the
Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF) on July 30 and the written
explanation of the "Mainland Affairs Council" on August 1 were
attempts to whitewash Lee Teng-hui's "two states" statement.
</P>
<P>
The commentary points out that the common point of the two
speeches was to take Lee's remarks as "laying foundation for equal
cross-Straits dialogue."
</P>
<P>
In fact, the speeches are serious distortions of the real
situation of the cross-Straits talks, the commentary notes.
</P>
<P>
It says that though the two sides of the Taiwan Straits have
not achieved reunification, the fact is that China's sovereignty
and territorial integrity remain unchanged.
</P>
<P>
This is a practical reflection of the situation of the cross-
Straits relations, it adds.
</P>
<P>
Since the Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits (
ARATS) and the SEF began their contacts and negotiations, the two
sides have taken the "One China" principle as the basis for
promotion of cross-Straits relations, though the two sides still
share different views on the political implications of the "One
China" principle.
</P>
<P>
The commentary emphasizes that denying and destroying the "One
China" principle is aimed at attempting to change the present
situation of cross-Straits relations, and China's sovereignty and
territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
It says that this is a challenge to peace and reunification,
and that the aim of Lee's "special state-to-state relations"
statement is to turn Taiwan into a "state" and then sperate it
from China.
</P>
<P>
The commentary says that the history of cross-Straits
negotiations indicates that Lee has been playing a role hindering
the talks.
</P>
<P>
Lee's "two states" statement, made before ARATS President Wang
Daohan's expected visit to Taiwan, has fundamentally destroyed the
foundation for cross-Straits negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Lee is putting the fundamental interests of Taiwan's people in
jeopardy, and that his aim is to ask for foreign intervention in
China's internal affairs and prepare for the "independence of
Taiwan," the commentary says.
</P>
<P>
It stresses that the Chinese people will firmly safeguard China
's sovereignty and territorial integrity, and that Lee Teng-hui's
splittism is doomed to failure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
