<DOCNO> XIE19990806.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Horti-Expo '99 Stimulates Yunnan Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The ongoing 1999 World
Horticulture Exposition being held in this capital city of
southwest China's Yunnan Province has played an important role in
promoting local tourism.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the provincial government indicate that Yunnan
received a total of 18 million domestic and overseas tourists in
the first half of this year, up 83 percent compared to the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The province generated 9.3 billion yuan in tourism revenue in
the January-June period, 34 percent more than in the previous year
's first six months.
</P>
<P>
Since the exposition opened May 1, more and more visitors have
been flocking to the province. To date, more than four million
people from all over the world have visited the exposition -- an
average of 80,000 visitors per day.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the exposition garden in Kunming, many tourism
sites, including Lijiang river, Diqing and Dali, in the province
have also become big attractions for tourists.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is China's last large international event before
the end of the century, said Li Jiating, deputy governor of Yunnan
Province.
</P>
<P>
The exposition is expected to receive about ten million
tourists during the six-month period, the official said, adding
that the whole province is expected to receive 30 million
travelers and earn 16.9 billion yuan from tourism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
