<HEADLINE> China Construction Bank Develops Merchant Banking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Construction Bank of China
held a symposium on merchant banking in this city of east China's
Fujian Province today to help promote financial aid for
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Merchant banking, which is called investment banking in the
United States, is a kind of financial service for enterprises in
the investment, enterprise merger, stock listing and other
financial fields.
</P>
<P>
The Construction Bank was among the first group of banks in
China to provide such services, and it has played an important
role in managing large investment projects in Beijing, Shanghai,
Jiangsu, Shandong, and other cities and provinces.
</P>
<P>
"Developing merchant banking will help the bank cater better to
the market demand and provide improved services for its customers,
" said a bank official.  
</P>
