<HEADLINE> Lull in Fighting in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 6 (Xinhua) -- There was no major fighting in
Afghanistan on Friday with the ruling Taliban militia controlling
heights overlooking the strategic Bagram airbase, sources from
Kabul said.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban's dominating positions rendered the airbase,
situated about 50 kilometers north of Kabul, unusable.
</P>
<P>
Forces loyal to opposition commander Ahmad Shah Masood Thursday
recaptured almost all the territory they had lost to the Taliban
during the last week and stopped at Bagram, the sources said.
