<HEADLINE> Rogers, AT&AMP;T, British Telecom PLC Bundle Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- AT&AMP;T Corp. and British Telecom PLC
have jointly bought a third of Canada's Rogers Cantel Mobile
Communications Inc. for 1.4 billion Canadian dollars (about 952
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
"The Gazette" newspaper of Canada said Friday that by swapping
cash and assets in an agreement Thursday, the venture would boost
Rogers as one of Canada's biggest wireless companies.
</P>
<P>
In another deal of the day, British Telecom paid 600 million
Canadian dollars (about 408 million U.S. dollars) for 30 percent
of AT&AMP;T's 31 percent share in AT&AMP;T Canada Inc., the report said.
</P>
<P>
Rogers Cantel and AT&AMP;T Canada said they would accelerate the
bundling and joint marketing of wired and wireless services for
Canadian business customers.
</P>
<P>
In response to the news Thursday, the Dominion Bond Rating
Service upgraded Rogers Cantel's rating, the report said without
detailing on the growth. 
