<HEADLINE> Palestinian Hamas Leader Announces Revival of Military Action </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The spiritual leader of the
Palestinian resistance movement Hamas, Sheikh Yassin, announced in
an interview published on Friday that his movement would revive
military action against Israel.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the French daily Liberation made in his
home in Gaza, Yassin said that the Palestinians need now more than
ever before to carry out resistance against Israeli occupation.
</P>
<P>
"The days which will come will show that the military branch (
of Hamas) always exists," he said, when asked whether the Hamas
has given up its armed struggle.
</P>
<P>
He said that to win cooperation from Hamas, Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat should abandon the Oslo agreements signed with
Israel first.
</P>
<P>
"If you want to negotiate with your enemy, you should be as
strong as he. If you negotiate with him in a state of weakness,
you will not achieve a peace process, but a process of
capitulation," he said.
</P>
<P>
Yassin said that the Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak is not "
a man of peace but a man of war."
</P>
<P>
"The proof is, he went to the United States talking about peace
but came back with 8 billion U.S. dollars worth of armaments," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"We should resist the occupation more than ever before, there
is no alternative to the military action today," he said. 
</P>
