<HEADLINE> Four Die, 150 Injured in Vietnam Soccer Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Four people died and 150 were
injured in traffic accidents in Ho Chi Minh City when a night of
celebrations following the Vietnam's victory over Myanmar on
Tuesday turned into tragedy, Vietnam's English daily Vietnam News
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam beat Myanmar 2-0 on Tuesday in the 20th Southeast Asian
Games qualifying match in Brunei.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese soccer fans poured onto the streets following the
win and the central Ho Chi Minh City was packed with motorcycles
which is a common sight in Vietnamese cities following an
international football win.
</P>
<P>
Many people injured were involved in illegal motorbike racing
that continued late into the night, with many of the victims
suffering serious head injuries, said police of the city, adding
that they were pelted with stones when they tried to break up
crowds that had gathered to watch the racing.
</P>
<P>
The city's hospitals were inundated with cases, with many
involving head traumas.
</P>
<P>
A total of 151 motorbikes were seized by police. 
</P>
