<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Int'l Cuisine Festival Slated for Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, August 6 (Xinhua) -- An International Cuisine
Festival, one of an extensive series of tourist promotion
activities, is slated to be staged in this capital of south China'
s Guangdong Province from September 24 to October 4.
</P>
<P>
Food in Guangdong, known as Yue-Style or Cantonese dishes, is
one of China's renowned cuisines-- as the old saying put it: the
Cantonese know what's good to eat. In Guangzhou these days, one
can now find dishes from nearly every corner of the globe.
</P>
<P>
All eight of China's traditional cooking styles will be
represented along a Chinese Cuisine Corridor during the festival,
where visitors can enjoy watching authentic cooking techniques,
and then savor the results.
</P>
<P>
Booths for foreign-style dishes from Japan, the Republic of
Korea, Thailand, Malaysia and countries of Europe and America also
will be represented.
</P>
<P>
Many food and tea-culture activities and performances also will
be on display throughout the festival. 
