<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Initiates Self-Protection Drive for Minors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A school to train minors how to
protect themselves, the first of its kind in China, was
established today in Daxing County near this Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that there are 360 million people under the age
of 18 in China. Governments at all levels have paid great
attention to their healthy growth, and made considerable efforts
to provide good education for them.
</P>
<P>
The school will provide a variety of training programs on self-
protection, self-rescue and mutual protection, with the aim of
helping youngsters to develop a healthy psychology and personality
when confronted with mental problems, disasters and accidents.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that more such schools will be set up across the
country.
</P>
<P>
Over the past ten years, the country has implemented a series
of regulations and laws on protecting minors against criminals.
</P>
<P>
While calling on the whole of society to join the protection
efforts, education experts also urged improving education in self-
protection for young persons.
</P>
<P>
Last November, a 14-year old girl was kidnapped and murdered
near her home in Beijing when she was watching a meteor shower,
according to a local educator.
</P>
<P>
The incident might have been avoided if the girl had had an
adequate knowledge of self-protection, he said.
</P>
<P>
A week after the incident, the city carried out an education
and promotion drive on juvenile self-protection. The relevant
departments set up a training camp, opened a 24-hour telephone
line, hosted a law seminar and recruited volunteers in this field.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
