<HEADLINE> Most Investors Satisfied With Shenzhen: Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 6 (Xinhua) --A sample survey shows that most
overseas investors are satisfied with the investment environment
of this special economic zone in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The overseas investors surveyed say that the stability of the
city's policies and legal guarantees regarding overseas investment
have given them confidence, and the rapid expansion of Shenzhen is
also creating many opportunities for business development.
</P>
<P>
The survey was done recently by the Shenzhen Overseas
Investment Promotion Bureau in order to study the situation of
overseas businesses in Shenzhen and offer constructive opinions to
help the city government work out policies conducive to improving
the city's investment environment.
</P>
<P>
The overseas investors surveyed also say that they believed
that tax policies affect their investment plans. Some of them
complained that administrative controls and comparatively higher
costs of labor limit the development of their businesses.
</P>
<P>
By April this year, Shenzhen approved 22,515 overseas-backed
projects, involving investments totalling 28.3 billion U.S.
dollars. So far, 18.03 billion dollars of overseas investment have
been pumped into the city.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 leading international companies have invested in
180 projects in Shenzhen, and many overseas investors have
increased their investments here.  
</P>
