<HEADLINE> Sichuan Makes Headway in Gas Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Sichuan
Province has turned out to be the country's largest gas production
base by discovering 520 billion cu m of gas reserves, according to
today's China Petroleum News.
</P>
<P>
The province has made significant achievements in gas
development by giving priority to exploring large and medium-sized
gas fields.
</P>
<P>
Through many years of exploration, the province has found 12
large-scale gas-bearing structures in its eastern part, covering a
total area of 335 sq km, with gas resources topping 100 billion cu
m.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the province has also made a major breakthrough in
gas exploration in the Kaijiang area, discovering five gas
deposits and nine gas-bearing structures, with estimated gas
resources totaling 260 billion cu m. 
