<HEADLINE> Macao Banks Ready to Pass Year 2000 Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Currency and Foreign Exchange
Authority of Macao has announced that the computer systems in
local banks are able to go smoothly through the year 2000 (Y2K).
</P>
<P>
The banks in Macao completed the testing of their computer
systems by the end of June, according to sources with the
authority.
</P>
<P>
Most of the banks set out to cope with the millennium bug
problem in 1997. Recently, the authority sent out questionnaires
to local banks to check their progress in handling the Y2K problem,
and the results turned out to be satisfying.
</P>
<P>
To make sure that the banks have the ability to deal with
unpredictable situation, the authority requires that the banks
work out emergency measures before September.
</P>
<P>
The sources with the authority noted that individual depositors
do not have to worry about their accounts, as the banks will back
up data for each client in advance. 
