<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Visitors in Tour Groups to Macao Rise Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The number of visitors in tour
groups to Macao exceeded 508,000 in the first half of the year, up
by 18.7 percent over the same period of 1998, the latest official
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released Friday by the Macao Census and
Statistics Department, the number of visitors in tour groups
soared 30.1 percent in June over the same month of last year.
</P>
<P>
The figures indicate that those coming from China's mainland
areas, Taiwan and Japan accounted for 82 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, 8,532 Macao residents, out of a population
of some 430,000, traveled to other places in tour groups in June.
The figure rose 42.5 percent over the same month of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The most favored destination of tour for Macao residents was
China's mainland areas which accommodated 54.8 percent of the
total tourists from Macao.
</P>
<P>
During the first half of this year as a whole, the number of
Macao residents traveling to other places in tour groups increased
19.5 percent over the same period of 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
