<HEADLINE> Beijing to Build New Railway in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Beijing will begin construction
of an urban railway line in October.
</P>
<P>
The line will run from Xizhimen in the west to Dongzhimen in
the east, through the city's high-tech zone in Zhongguancun and
Huilongguan. The 40-km line will have 16 stations.
</P>
<P>
The project is to be carried out in two stages at a cost of 5.
81 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The first stage, from Xizhimen to Huilongguan, will be
completed by the end of 2001, and the second stage from
Huilongguan to Dongzhimen by 2005.
</P>
<P>
The project was approved by the State Council earlier this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
