<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Form Netpreneurs Community </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will undertake a
census of "netpreneurs" and form a community among them to ensure
the success of the country's Multimedia Super Corridor (MSC).
</P>
<P>
The census, to be carried out by the National Information
Technology Council (NITC), would take six months to a year in
order to have a good database for the purpose of analysis, NITC
Secretary Mohd Azzman Shariffadeen told reporters after the launch
of Multimedia Asia 1999 (MMA'99) here Friday.
</P>
<P>
"Netpreneurs" have been described as those making money and
surviving through the Internet.
</P>
<P>
By having this kind of database, the NITC could link
"netpreneurs" and this would then open a lot of opportunities to
them for sharing and partnerships, he said.
</P>
<P>
MMA'99 to be held from September 22 to 26 is an official
conference and exhibition with the theme "Re-aligning for a New
Economy", aimed at promoting the MSC. 
</P>
