<HEADLINE> Role of U.N. Organizations Should Be Increased: Jiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIDAIHE, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here today that to help realize the comprehensive economic
and social development of developing countries, the role of the
United Nations (U.N.) organizations should be increased.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to continue conducting and reinforcing
cooperation with the U.N. and its organizations, Jiang said in a
meeting with administrator Mark Brown of the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) this morning in this summer coastal
resort of Beidaihe, about 300 kilometers east of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The multi-lateral assistance organizations of the U.N., as
major forces for world development and cooperation, have important
and active roles to play in this aspect, Jiang said, reiterating
China's consistent support for the U.N.'s role in world affairs
and the purpose and principles of the U.N. Charter.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China has made considerable achievements in
economic construction and social development since 1978 when it
initiated the reform and opening-up policy, and cooperation with
the UNDP has been fruitful.
</P>
<P>
This cooperation has served as a channel for China in learning
foreign scientific and technological developments, absorbing
advanced technology, and drawing on advanced management experience,
and it has also assisted China in resolving problems concerning
reform, opening up, and economic and social development, the
Chinese president said.
</P>
<P>
As the 21st century draws near, peace and development should be
worldwide goals, Jiang said, adding that all countries should
cooperate with equality and respect for diversity.
</P>
<P>
China opposes the idea that all countries must deal with
different issue in the same way and by the same approach, he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government and people are pursuing an independent
foreign policy of peace, and consider the development of the
national economy and the promotion of development worldwide as
their primary task, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that only when the vast developing countries
achieve comprehensive economic and social developments, can world
peace and stability enjoy a solid foundation.
</P>
<P>
Brown said he is happy with China's achievements over the past
20 years, and satisfied with the UNDP's fruitful cooperation with
China during that period.
</P>
<P>
He said the UNDP highly appreciates the Chinese government's
support for its work, and it is willing to join with the Chinese
government to contribute to the reform, opening and modernization
drive ongoing in the country.
</P>
<P>
Brown is visiting China as guest of China's Minister of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation Shi Guangsheng. 
</P>
</TEXT>
