<HEADLINE> Information Industry Officials Slam Lee Teng-hui's Splittist Remarks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Leading Chinese officials and
experts in the field of information denounced Lee Teng-hui's
splittist remarks here today, saying that his "two states"
statement has destroyed healthy cross-Straits cooperation, and
they urged him to stop all activities splitting the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jichuan, Minister of Information Industry told a seminar
that Lee's "two states" or "special state-to-state relations"
statement has further exposed his nature as one that wants to
split China's territory and sovereignty, enraging Chinese people
both at home and overseas.
</P>
<P>
He said President Jiang Zemin reiterated China's solemn stand
on the Taiwan issue in a recent telephone conversation with U.S.
President Bill Clinton, which fully conveyed the determination of
the Chinese people to safeguard the territorial and sovereign
integrity of China.
</P>
<P>
Under the guidance of the "peaceful reunification and one
country, two systems" principles, cross-Straits trade and
personnel exchanges have been expanding in recent years, and
progress in direct links for mail, shipping and trade has also
been made, said Wu.
</P>
<P>
So far, the GSM mobile phone, ISDN, and other
telecommunications businesses have been opened between the two
sides of the Taiwan Straits, and post and telecommunications
volume has also been on the rise in recent years.
</P>
</TEXT>
