<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seven Die in Flood in Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Seven people have been killed and
dozens severely injured in a flood that hit the eastern part of
northwest China's Qinghai Province over the past three days,
according to a local official.
</P>
<P>
The flood, caused by heavy rains and hail, damaged a large
number of houses, highways, railways, and crop areas, said Sun Lin,
an official with the Qinghai Civil Administration Department.
</P>
<P>
He said the flood swept across five counties and over 20
townships and 100 villages, affecting more than 100,000 people.
</P>
<P>
The flood also inundated 16,000 mu (about 1,000 hectares) of
farmland, destroying hundreds of hectares of cultivated land and
causing over 400 houses to collapse.
</P>
<P>
Mountain torrents triggered by heavy rains also damaged some
road beds in the area, suspending operations on three sections of
the Qinghai-Lanzhou railway line and leaving passengers on the
line stranded for nine hours.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers have been sent to the area to evacuate flood
victims and are working round the clock to repair damages, Sun
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
