<DOCNO> XIE19990806.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines Creates Committee for ASEAN Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada has created a national organizing committee for the Third
Informal Summit of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN-NOC) to be held in Manila in November.
</P>
<P>
The Presidential Palace said Friday in a news release that
Estrada issued the July Administrative Order No. 76 which
authorizes the ASEAN-NOC to supervise preparations for the summit
and its related meetings.
</P>
<P>
"The Philippines has committed to promoting peace and
prosperity in Southeast Asia by maintaining and strengthening its
relations with the member countries of ASEAN," he said in issuing
the administrative order.
</P>
<P>
The president also pointed out the Philippines has made ASEAN
the cornerstone of its foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN-NOC will be chaired by the secretary of the
Department of Foreign Affairs (DFA), with the executive secretary
as co-chairman. The other members of the committee are the
secretaries of the country's major departments.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN-NOC's main task is to formulate and recommend to the
president a work program on the preparations for the Third
Informal Summit by the end of October.
</P>
<P>
It would then implement the work plan and supervise and monitor
all activities related to the preparations for the summit, and
seek assistance from officials of the national and local
governments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
