<HEADLINE> Indonesia Starts Bidding Drive for 2006 Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia set off its campaign
for the 2006 Asian Games on Friday as its National Olympic
Committee presented its bid to leaders of the Southeast Asian (SEA)
Games Federation on the eve of the Brunei SEA Games.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia entered the battle for the Asiad just two days after
another Southeast Asian country Malaysia launched its official bid.
</P>
<P>
The United Arab Emirates, India, Kuwait and Hong Kong of China
has also announced its intention of hosting the regional Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Olympic Committee will decide on the winner in
November 2000. The bidders are expected to submit the
administration requirements at the general assembly in Kuwait in
November this year.
</P>
<P>
Bangkok staged the Games last year and the 2002 Asiad will be
in Pusan, South Korea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
