<DOCNO> XIE19990806.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two 1,000-year-old Turtles Found in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Two large turtles, which are
believed to be over 1,000 years old, have attracted more than two
million domestic and overseas visitors since they were discovered
in June at a temple in the city of Dali in southwest China's
Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The two turtles, which were first mistaken for two large stones
by monks of the Wuwei Temple, weigh 90 kg each. Experts confirm
that the turtles are the largest of their kind ever found in China.
The tortoise-shell of the two turtles is about 80 cm. long.
</P>
<P>
One turtle is 88 cm long, 78 cm wide and 40 cm tall, the other,
86 cm long, 76 cm wide and 36 cm tall, and they are both now being
kept in the temple. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
