<DOCNO> XIE19990806.0203 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Li Hongzhi Defrauds People of Money </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Public Security Bureau in
Northeast China's Jilin Province recently discovered new evidence
of the fraudulent behavior of Li Hongzhi, the head of the Falun
Gong cult.
</P>
<P>
This evidence shows that Li defrauded people of large sums of
money by selling books and audio and video products on Falun Gong.
In 1995, Li and his followers made nearly 100,000 yuan from the
sales of a book on Falun Gong. Li Hongzhi and his key members also
reaped more than 300,000 yuan by selling audio and video tapes of
his lectures.
</P>
<P>
Li also accumulated wealth by running Falun Gong study classes
in Changchun, and earned 400,000 yuan there since 1992.
</P>
<P>
According to Tang Xuehua, a former key number of Falun Gong,
Li collected no less than 1,500,000 yuan by running Falun Gong
study classes in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Former Falun Gong cult members in north China's Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region said that the Falun Gong organization there also
collected a large amount of money from its practitioners in a "
pyramid" scheme.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990806.0204 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most Chinese Cities Report Good Air Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Most Chinese cities reported
stable air quality this week, but some parts of northern and
northwest China suffered from suspended particles, according to a
report released today by China Environment Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
From July 30 to August 5, five cities including Lanzhou, Xining,
Hohhot, Taiyuan, and Guiyang reported slight air pollution.
Yinchuan, Chongqing, Guangzhou, Tianjin, Shenyang, Beijing,
Shanghai, and 23 other cities reported good air quality.
</P>
<P>
Eleven cities including Nanning, Guilin, Wenzhou, Suzhou,
Dalian, Zhanjiang, Ningbo, Zhuhai, Xiamen, Beihai, and Haikou
enjoyed excellent air quality during the week.
</P>
<P>
The major problem in Beijing, Lanzhou, Xining, and some other
cities was suspended particles, while in Guangzhou and Shanghai it
was nitrogen oxide, and in Chongqing it was sulfur dioxide.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
