<HEADLINE> BOC Operates Smoothly in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) made good
progress in its major business activities in the first half of
this year thanks to improvements in asset quality and increasing
capital strength.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the BOC said today that in the first six months,
the bank's newly increased loans reached 48.77 billion yuan, an
increase of 25.48 billion yuan over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
These loans have mainly been channeled to key enterprises in
the telecommunications, high-tech, transportation, and energy
sectors, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He said that by the end of June, the bank's deposits increased
9.94 percent over the end of last year, while the amount of
outstanding loans increased 2.82 percent.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the BOC also made large strides in credit card
issuance, foreign exchange trading, bond investment, derivative
products trading, and other business sectors, he said, adding that
great efforts were also made in providing integrated financial
services for corporate clients, launching consumer credit
businesses, and developing investment banking.  
</P>
