<HEADLINE> Micronesia Reiterates Commitment to One China Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Micronesia's Foreign Secretary
Epel K. Ilon Friday reiterated the country's commitment to the
"One China" policy.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Xu Jun, Chinese Ambassador to the
Federated States of Micronesia (FSM), Ilon said that the FSM
government has all along adhered to the One China policy and will
continue to pursue the same policy in the future.
</P>
<P>
Talking about Lee Teng-hui's recent separatist remarks and the
situation across the Taiwan straits, Ilon said that the FSM
government holds that there is only one China in the world and the
government of the People's Republic of China is the sole legal
government representing the whole of China.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan is only a province of China and the FSM government did
not have in the past and will not have in the future any official
relations with Taiwan, he said. 
