<HEADLINE> Yunnan Woos Foreign Investors to Develop Mineral Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Yunnan Province in southwest
China has recently approved a regulation encouraging overseas
investors to explore and develop mineral resources.
</P>
<P>
In line with the regulation, overseas businesses will be able
to explore and develop mineral resources in Yunnan after obtaining
the requisite authorization.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan, known as the "kingdom of nonferrous metal" because of
its special geological features, has proven deposits of 130 kinds
of minerals, and its reserves of tin, zinc, copper, and lead are
among the richest in the country.
</P>
<P>
However, these abundant mineral and nonferrous metal resources
have not been fully developed due to inadequate investment and
poor management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
