<HEADLINE> Cotton Yarn Exports Rise in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 6 (Xinhua) -- India's cotton yarn exports
registered a positive growth in terms of volume as well as value,
for the first six months of 1999.
</P>
<P>
According to the Commerce Ministry, cotton yarn shipments
during the period were higher at 264.17 million kilogram against
230.56 million kilogram exported in the corresponding period of
last year, an increase of 14.58 percent.
</P>
<P>
In terms of value, exports increased to 317.02 billion rupees
(7.37 billion U.S. dollars) from 287.776 billion rupees (6.69
billion dollars) during January and June of 1998, an increase of
10.16 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
