<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Float 30 New Insurance Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Thirty more new insurance
companies, including 19 general and 11 life insurance ones, will
be floated in Bangladesh in the private sector soon, The
Bangladesh Observer daily newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Commerce has already given pre-approval to
these companies under the Insurance Act. After receiving the final
approval of the prime minister, the ministry sent the list of the
30 insurance companies to the chief controller of insurance on
June 22 this year.
</P>
<P>
Some terms and conditions are required to be fulfilled to get
registration before the floating of an insurance company,
according to the Insurance Act. One condition is that the sponsor
or the promoter shall neither be a bank defaulter nor a director
of any other companies, and the dependents of any sponsor or
director shall not be a director of the insurance company.
</P>
<P>
Besides, an amount of 150 million taka (about 2.92 million U.S.
dollars) is required as paid-up capital to start a general
insurance, of which 60 percent will be collected through public
shares and the rest from the sponsors or the promoters. In the
case of floating a life insurance, 75 million taka (about 1.52
million dollars) is needed.
</P>
<P>
The deadline for meeting the above terms and conditions for
registration has been fixed by the chief controller of insurance
on August 8.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are 24 general insurance companies and seven
life insurance companies including one foreign life insurance
company in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
