<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes Over 5,000 Kilos of Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized
5,150 kilograms of narcotic drugs, including 212.97 kg of heroin
and 930.2 kg of opium, in the first seven months of this year, the
country's Central Committee for Drug Abuse Control (CCDAC) said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Army units, police and the customs also confiscated 179.07 kg
of marijuana, 186.97 liters of phensedyl and 13.715 million
tablets of amphetamine stimulant drug, the CCDAC said at a press
conference here.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the authorities punished 3,844 persons
involved in 2,804 drug-related cases, it added.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, 10,794 kg of narcotic drugs,
including 403.8 kg of heroin and 5,393.6 kg of opium as well as
16.02 million stimulant drug tablets, were seized in the country
in 1998 with 4,845 drug offenders punished in connection with
3,546 related cases. 
</P>
