<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Holds "Women in Business" Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka on Friday inaugurated a
three-day "Women in Business" trade fair to improve the potential
of rural women to develop their income-generation activities and
standards of living.
</P>
<P>
Over 100 local and Indian women exhibited their wide-ranging
products at the fair, which is organized by Sri Lanka's Women's
Chamber of Industry and Commerce (WCIC).
</P>
<P>
The fair is expected to help rural women to expand their trade
links and also generate foreign exchange for the country.
</P>
<P>
The first vice chairperson of WCIC, Maya Senanayake, said that
they were encouraged to conduct such fairs after the success of
the first one in 1988.
</P>
<P>
The Internal and International Commerce Ministry has instructed
export development officials to install a "cyber trader" and
Internet facilities at the fair to help woman entrepreneurs
develop their business contacts and find new markets abroad.
</P>
