<HEADLINE> Northwest Cargo Plane Makes Emergency Landing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A Northwest Airlines cargo airplane
from the United States was forced to make an emergency landing at
Narita Airport Friday because of a fire in the engine, airport
officials said.
</P>
<P>
The jumbo jet landed safely at the airport, which is located
east of Tokyo, at 11:24 a.m. local time (0224GMT).
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out in one of the engines three minutes after it
took off from the airport at 10:52 a.m.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the incident is under investigation, Northeast
Airlines said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
