<HEADLINE> hke080607-Colombo to Host Largest Indo-Sri Lanka Trade Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Colombo is to host an INTRAD
Millennium Exhibition in May next year, the fourth and the largest
in the series of Indo-Sri Lanka industrial and trade exhibitions,
officials said Friday.
</P>
<P>
An official of Sri Lanka's National Chamber of Commerce said
the exhibition aims to increase trade between the two countries
and establish better trade relations within South Asia.
</P>
<P>
INTRAD, introduced by the chamber in 1996, aims to project the
image of Sri Lanka, its capability and potential in the commercial
sector particularly in manufacturing, trading and marketing of
goods and service.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, from May 26 to 28, 2000, is expected to promote
Sri Lanka as a hub for exchange of information, technology,
products and services within South Asia.
</P>
<P>
It will also seek to give exposure to Sri Lankan industries in
the entire region. Local entrepreneurs will be assisted to find
partners and agents in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
