<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Close Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, August 5 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange
closed up Thursday with the Benchmark IPC index surging 7.88
points, or 0.15 percent, at 5,150.79.
</P>
<P>
But the index of Mexico, the second largest one closed down 1.
38 points or 0.48 percent, at 289.05.
</P>
<P>
Operators changed 74.415 million shares for about 124.8 million
U.S. dollars, against 68.260 million shares worth 140.208 million
dollars on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.60 to one dollar for
sale and 9.30 for purchase in the main exchange houses of the
Mexico city, compared with 9.55 for sale and 9.25 for purchase on
Wednesday. 
</P>
