<DOCNO> XIE19990806.0273 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Agricultural Bank Improves Management Of Corporate Credit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Agricultural Bank of China (
ABC) issued guidelines today on managing corporate credit to
improve efficiency, minimize risks, and to support the healthy
development of corporations.
</P>
<P>
All ABC branches need to provide support for enterprises and to
minimize financial risks. They need to unify credit and management
in providing credit to corporations, according to the guidelines.
</P>
<P>
A bank spokesman says that priority will be given to
enterprises with a good record and good development prospects that
follow the state's industrial policies.
</P>
<P>
The guidelines also restrict lending to enterprises that are
poorly managed or have a poor credit history.
</P>
<P>
ABC is one of China's four large state-owned commercial banks.
It reported an increase of 60.3 billion yuan (7.3 billion US
dollars) in outstanding loans in the first half and an increase of
151.4 billion yuan (18.2 billion US dollars) in deposits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
