<HEADLINE> Chinese, Japanese Youth To Increase Mutual Understanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A 47-member delegation from Japan
headed by Ishi Yoshiya, the president of Aichi University, arrived
here today for a three-week extracurricular and goodwill visit.
</P>
<P>
During the stay the visitors will be split up in five groups
and will have a look at enterprise management, women workers'
conditions, urban life, and countryside conditions to better
understand the lives of the people of Beijing. They will also
learn about the conditions at state-run enterprises, and the
production and labor relations of overseas-funded enterprises.
</P>
<P>
They are scheduled to hold discussions with their Chinese
counterparts at a Sino-Japanese youth seminar.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is here at the invitation of the All-China
Federation of Trade Unions.
</P>
<P>
Aichi University has friendly ties with Chinese institutions of
higher learning including Beijing Language and Culture University
and Nankai University.  
