<HEADLINE> Facts and Figures: Foreign Trade of Top 10 Provinces, Municipalities (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Following are the latest facts
and figures about China's top ten trade provinces and
municipalities in the first six months of this year, provided by
the General Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
 -- The trade volume of Guangdong Province dropped 3.2 percent
to 60.505 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports decreased 12.3 percent
to 32.254 billion U.S. dollars and imports grew 9.9 percent to 28.
251 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
 -- The trade volume of Shanghai increased 23.1 percent to 16.
664 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports and imports went up 17.2
percent and 29.2 percent to 8.129 billion U.S. dollars and 8.535
billion U.S. dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
 -- The trade volume of Beijing went up 13.7 percent to 15.570
billion U.S. dollars. Its exports declined 10.1 percent to 4.408
billion U.S. dollars and imports soared 27 percent to 11.162
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
 -- The trade volume of Jiangsu Province increased 12.9
percent to 13.390 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports and imports
went up 12.7 percent and 13.1 percent to 7.729 billion U.S.
dollars and 5.661 billion U.S. dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
-- The trade volume of Shandong Province grew 2.3 percent to 8.
321 billion U.S. dollars. Its exports and imports increased 3.6
percent and 0.4 percent to 5.180 billion U.S. dollars and 3.141
billion respectively.
</P>
