<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil to Increase Gasoline Price </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Brazil announced a hike of 9
percent on gasoline prices on August 8, which will be the fifth
price increase so far this year.
</P>
<P>
The new price on a gallon of standard gasoline will increase
from the previous level of 74 U.S. cents to 80.7 cents.
</P>
<P>
The Finance, Mines and Energy Ministries said the increase was
to adjust the internal price of gasoline to meet the price shift
on the international market.
</P>
<P>
Brazil imports over 700,000 barrels of gasoline every day to
satisfy a daily demand of 1.8 million barrels. 
</P>
</TEXT>
