<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WB-Aided Beijing Central Heating Plant Completed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 6 (Xinhua) -- This capital of China has
completed the building of a large plant for providing central
heating for an area of five million square meters in Haidian
District, aided by a World Bank loan.
</P>
<P>
It is one of the major projects arranged by the municipal
government for curbing serious air pollution in Beijing in the
winter season.
</P>
<P>
The plant cost around 20 million U.S. dollars to build,
including a World Bank loan of 9.1 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The project, located at Zhichun Road, could replace over 400
coal-fueled boilers and greatly reduce the air pollution in the
surrounding area in winter.
</P>
<P>
The central heating plant takes up an area of 11 ha, and is
fueled by natural gas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
