<HEADLINE> Frenchman Djorkaeff Moves to Kaiserslautern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 5 (Xinhua) -- French midfielder Youri Djorkaeff
will make his debut at the Bundesliga with Kaiserslautern
following a frustrating season with Italian club Inter Milan.
</P>
<P>
Kaiserslautern board member Gerhard Herzog said on Thursday
that both sides had reached an agreement and Djorkaeff could be in
the uniform of the 1997-1998 German champions in their opening
match of the season against Borussia Dortmund at homecourt on
August 14.
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old was expected to sign a three-year contract this
weekend. According to press reports, Kaiserslautern will pay Inter
around four million marks ($2.21 million) for the newcomer, who
will receive an annual salary of around 3.6 million marks.
</P>
<P>
Djorkaeff, who joined Inter Milan from Paris St Germain in 1996,
was a regular in the Inter first team until this season, during
which he was often left on the bench. 
</P>
</TEXT>
