<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuban Sports Minister Issues Statement of Principle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WINNIPEG, Canada, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Cuban Minister of Sports
Humberto Rodriquez Gonzalez Thursday reiterated that the country's
athletes are competing under "an atmosphere of hostility" at the
13th Pan American Games in a statement of principle following
world record holder Javier Sotomayor tested positive for Cocaine
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
"The main reason why I'm here today is to speak of performances
of our delegation, which unfortunately have not been the main
center of our Games," Gonzalez said at a news conference here
today.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban athletes came here to compete in the sports, to
defend their main medals, which are "the medals of our country",
and to underline their spirits of discipline, pereverence and
concentration.
</P>
<P>
And the job so far has been "proficiently and exellently done",
said Gonzalez.
</P>
<P>
But the local media gave priority to other non-sports issues,
in which he implied the reporting on defections -- a male gymnast
asking for asylum Tuesday is the sixth known case.
</P>
<P>
In his marathon speech, Gonzalez once again pointed out the
Cuban delegation are here subject to such a pressure and difficult
situation they have never had experienced before where athletes
were being stalked, provoked and swamped by phonecalls and
personal messages.
</P>
<P>
However, he admitted, they did receive repect of the Canadian
audience, which is a "extremely good reponse".
</P>
<P>
"Medals-winning is not the most important thing for us. Dignity
is," Gongzalez said.
</P>
<P>
"But unfortunately, the most basic respect did not come at the
right place at the right time," he said.
</P>
<P>
When asked about whether there was hostility from the PASO
laboratory in Montreal, which reported a positive drug test result
for Sotomayor, Gongzalez said:" We don't have any proof yet."
</P>
<P>
He then went on to reiterate they totally believe Sotomayor is
an innocent man.
</P>
<P>
"He said he was being victimized and fell under a trap,"
Gongzalez quoted Sotomayor as saying.
</P>
<P>
"It's unfair for an athlete giving so much to the sports world
to be subject to such a result," he said.
</P>
<P>
Dr.Mario Granda, chief doctor of the Cuban delegation, said
yesterday there is a manipulaton in the Sotomayor case.
</P>
<P>
But Gongzalez today preferred "manuveur" to "manipulation".
</P>
<P>
"I've never said manipulation," Gongzalez said. " What I said
was manuveur."
</P>
<P>
Despite "all the manuveurs which has been created", Gongzalez
ensured that the Cuban delegation will prepare themselves for a
good finale and leave the central Canadian city on a high-note.
</P>
<P>
"But we'll forever remember we've been subject to such a
pressure,to such a great amount of hostility," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
