<HEADLINE> Tyson to Face Douglas Again in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 5 (Xinhua) -- Mike Tyson is seeking a
revenge on his biggest rival Buster Douglas in his latest comeback
fight on October 2 at the MGM Grand Garden in Las Vegas, a press
report said today.
</P>
<P>
Tyson's boxing adviser, Shelly Finkel, was flying from New York
to Scottsdale, to watch Tyson train but was out of reach for
comment.
</P>
<P>
Douglas, 38, made a big surprise on February 11, 1990 when he
knocked out the then undisputed heavyweight champion Tyson in the
10th round. Douglas went off as a 42-1 underdog, but dominated the
bout and put Tyson out with a series of punches to chalk up one of
the most shocking upsets in boxing history.
</P>
<P>
Douglas lost the title to Evander Holyfield in his first
defense, then retired for six years.
</P>
<P>
He made a comeback but looked like a shadow of himself in
recent bouts. He was knocked out in the opening round by Lou
Savarese in June 1998 and won his last two fights by knickout
against nondescript opposition.
</P>
<P>
Tyson, who knocked down Frans Botha in the fifth round on
January 16 at the MGM, is going to make his third return to boxing.
The former heavyweight champion was put into jail after assaulting
two men following a traffic accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
