<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuador Catches More Tuna in the Pacific </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, August 5 (Xinhua)-- With a volume of 110,000 metric
tons, Ecuador has become the country with the largest capture of
tuna in the Eastern Pacific Ocean.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador's taking represent 30 percent of those made by all the
countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
However, Ecuador will not be allowed to go on at this speed,
because the maximum quota the Inter-American Commission of Tropic
Tuna gives Ecuador is 40,000 metric tons. If Ecuador break the
rules, the country's fishing activity would be suspended in year
2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
