<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Philippine newspapers Friday.
</P>
<P>
Malaya:
</P>
<P>
-- The death toll from landslides and floods caused by
continuous rains in the northern Philippines since Sunday rose to
67 as of Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin:
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine President Joseph Estrada vowed Thursday that he
will institute measures to prevent tragic landslides in the
country as he formed an investigating team to determine the
liability for a landslide tragedy in Rizal province that killed 27
people.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Daily Inquirer:
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippine government announced Thursday that inflation
in July was at 5.7 percent, unchanged from the revised 5.7 percent
figure for June, and analysts said the data suggested interest
rates would remain steady. 
</P>
</TEXT>
